ArcelorMittal, Imperial, Super Group May Move: South Africa Stocks Preview

-- B y   S i k o n a t h i   M a n t s h a n t s h a
-- 
2011-02-23T06:00:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-22/imperial-kelly-group-super-group-south-african-equity-preview.html
The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in  South Africa .  Stock symbols are in parentheses after company names and
prices are from the last close.  South Africa’s FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index dropped the
most since Jan. 28, losing 362.47, or 1.1 percent, to 32,444.20
at the 5 p.m. close in Johannesburg.    ArcelorMittal South Africa Ltd . (ACL SJ): The continent’s
largest steelmaker may face increased competition in South
Africa after Lazarus Zim’s Afripalm Resources signed a deal with
Steel Authority of India Ltd. to build a 21 billion rand ($2.9
billion) mill,  Business Day  reported. Shares in the unit of
ArcelorMittal decreased 0.3 percent to 90.23 rand.    Imperial Holdings Ltd . (IPL SJ): The country’s largest
auto-dealer said net income rose to 1.38 billion rand in the six
months to Dec. 31, from 1.01 billion rand a year earlier. Shares
in the company fell 16 cents, or 0.1 percent, to 114.25 rand.  Kelly Group Ltd. (KEL SJ): The staffing company holds an
investor and quarterly earnings update. Shares in Kelly declined
35 cents, or 8.1 percent, to 4 rand.    Rolfes Technology Holdings Ltd . (RLF SJ): The color pigment
manufacturing company said sales in the six months through
December climbed 18 percent to 228.7 million rand. Shares in the
company were unchanged at 1.75 rand.  Super Group Ltd. (SPG SJ): The transport services provider
said headline earnings from continuing operations more than
doubled to 154.4 million rand in the six months through
December, from 71.9 million rand a year earlier. Super Group
added 1 cent, or 1.4 percent, to 75 cents.    Transpaco Ltd . (TPC SJ): The South African paper and
packaging distributor said fiscal first-half earnings per share
increased 14 percent to 1.42 rand. Shares in the company dropped
3.7 percent to 13.20 rand.  Shares or American depositary receipts of the following
South African companies closed as follows:  Anglo American Plc (AAUKY US) fell 1.2 percent to $25.64.
AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (AU US) added 0.7 percent to $47.88. BHP
Billiton Ltd. (BBL US) lost 0.7 percent to $76.79. DRDGold Ltd.
(DROOY US) gained 0.2 percent to $4.63. Gold Fields Ltd. (GFI
US) was unchanged at $17.29. Harmony Gold Mining Co. (HMY US)
added 1.1 percent to $11.36. Impala Platinum Holdings (IMPUY US)
lost 3.3 percent to $29.20. Sappi Ltd. (SPP US) retreated almost
3 percent $5.21. Sasol Ltd. (SSL US) gained 0.3 percent to
$51.40.  To contact the reporter on this story:
